verses.text_plain: Bel boweth down, Nebo stoopeth, their idols were upon the beasts, and upon the cattle: your carriages were heavy loaden; they are a burden to the weary beast.
verses.verse_html: 1Bel boweth down, Nebo stoopeth, their idols were upon the beasts, and upon the cattle: your carriages were heavy loaden; they are a burden to the weary beast.

verses.text_plain: They stoop, they bow down together; they could not deliver the burden, but themselves are gone into captivity.
verses.verse_html:
2They stoop, they bow down together; they could not deliver the burden, but themselves are gone into captivity. ▼
▼ themselves: Heb. their soul

footnotes.body_html: ▼ themselves: Heb. their soul

verses.text_plain: Hearken unto me, O house of Jacob, and all the remnant of the house of Israel, which are borne by me from the belly, which are carried from the womb:
verses.verse_html: 3Hearken unto me, O house of Jacob, and all the remnant of the house of Israel, which are borne by me from the belly, which are carried from the womb:

verses.text_plain: And even to your old age I am he; and even to hoar hairs will I carry you: I have made, and I will bear; even I will carry, and will deliver you.
verses.verse_html: 4And even to your old age I am he; and even to hoar hairs will I carry you: I have made, and I will bear; even I will carry, and will deliver you.

verses.text_plain: To whom will ye liken me, and make me equal, and compare me, that we may be like?
verses.verse_html: 5To whom will ye liken me, and make me equal, and compare me, that we may be like?

tokens.text: me, that we may be like

verses.text_plain: They lavish gold out of the bag, and weigh silver in the balance, and hire a goldsmith; and he maketh it a god: they fall down, yea, they worship.
verses.verse_html: 6They lavish gold out of the bag, and weigh silver in the balance, and hire a goldsmith; and he maketh it a god: they fall down, yea, they worship.

verses.text_plain: They bear him upon the shoulder, they carry him, and set him in his place, and he standeth; from his place shall he not remove: yea, one shall cry unto him, yet can he not answer, nor save him out of his trouble.
verses.verse_html: 7They bear him upon the shoulder, they carry him, and set him in his place, and he standeth; from his place shall he not remove: yea, one shall cry unto him, yet can he not answer, nor save him out of his trouble.

tokens.text: him, and set him in his place
unto him, yet can he not answer

verses.text_plain: Remember this, and shew yourselves men: bring it again to mind, O ye transgressors.
verses.verse_html: 8Remember this, and shew yourselves men: bring it again to mind, O ye transgressors.

verses.text_plain: Remember the former things of old: for I am God, and there is none else; I am God, and there is none like me,
verses.verse_html: 9Remember the former things of old: for I am God, and there is none else; I am God, and there is none like me,

verses.text_plain: Declaring the end from the beginning, and from ancient times the things that are not yet done, saying, My counsel shall stand, and I will do all my pleasure:
verses.verse_html: 10Declaring the end from the beginning, and from ancient times the things that are not yet done, saying, My counsel shall stand, and I will do all my pleasure:

verses.text_plain: Calling a ravenous bird from the east, the man that executeth my counsel from a far country: yea, I have spoken it, I will also bring it to pass; I have purposed it, I will also do it.
verses.verse_html:
11Calling a ravenous bird from the east, the man that executeth my counsel from a far country: yea, I have spoken it, I will also bring it to pass; I have purposed it, I will also do it. ▼
▼ that…: Heb. of my counsel

tokens.text: it to pass; I have purposed

footnotes.body_html: ▼ that…: Heb. of my counsel

verses.text_plain: Hearken unto me, ye stouthearted, that are far from righteousness:
verses.verse_html: 12Hearken unto me, ye stouthearted, that are far from righteousness:

verses.text_plain: I bring near my righteousness; it shall not be far off, and my salvation shall not tarry: and I will place salvation in Zion for Israel my glory.
verses.verse_html: 13I bring near my righteousness; it shall not be far off, and my salvation shall not tarry: and I will place salvation in Zion for Israel my glory.

tokens.text: it shall not be far off
